title: Day One
subtitle: ECCE App Challenge 2018 - University of Calgary

about.aboutContent:
How to Use This App

Basics:

Click and drag to pan around the map. Pinch or scroll to zoom.

Search:

To search for a place, type a name into the search bar. To search within a category, select from the drop-down menu to the left of the search bar.

Bookmarks:

Areas of interest for newcomers to Canada have been bookmarked for your convenience. Click on the book icon to see where other newcomers have gone on their Day One in Canada.

Direction:

Directly below the book icon, the directions icon lets you plot a trip to and from any of the given places on this map.

Query:

The Day One map is populated with all the essentials of getting settled in Calgary, so find exactly what you need by clicking on the Query icon, picking a category from the drop-down menu, and typing in a specific sub-category such as Daycare or Walk-In Clinics. The full list of valid entries can be found under each search bar.

Near Me:

Findthe closest library, family doctor, or career centre to you by selecting from the categories from the drop-down menu and choosing your desired proximity in kilometres.
